article.description: — Josh Reaves' 20 points helped Mount St. Mary's defeat Saint Francis (PA) 72-65 on Friday night.
article.headline: Reaves scores 20, Mount St. Mary's takes down Saint Francis (PA) 72-65
article.linkText: Reaves scores 20, Mount St. Mary's takes down Saint Francis (PA) 72-65
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- — Josh Reaves' 20 points helped Mount St. Mary's defeat Saint Francis (PA) 72-65 on Friday night. Reaves was 7 of 9 shooting (6 for 8 from 3-point range) for the Mountaineers (4-6). Dakota Leffew scored 14 points and added five rebounds and three steals. Deshayne Montgomery had 14 points and was 6 of 10 shooting (1 for 4 from 3-point range). The Red Flash (4-7) were led in scoring by Cam Gregory, who finished with 20 points. Aaron Talbert added 16 points. Carlos Lopez Jr. also recorded 12 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
